para.verbatim: Child classes must define this method, which defines how the ``default_name`` is set.

Requires that at least one :class:`ParseExpression` is found. If two expressions match, the expression that matches the longest string will be used. May be constructed using the ``'^'`` operator.
Example::
# construct Or using '^' operator
number = Word(nums) ^ Combine(Word(nums) + '.' + Word(nums)) print(number.search_string("123 3.1416 789"))
prints::
[['123'], ['3.1416'], ['789']]
